‚ÄúA lot of people ask me how my mother felt when I became PM, but by then the name ‚ÄòModi‚Äô was in the air, my photos were being printed and there was a lot of excitement all over. But I think the bigger milestone for her, was when I became CM. 
I was living in Delhi when I found out. Before taking the oath, I went straight to see her in Ahmedabad, where she lives with my brother.
By then she had already found out that I had become the CM, but to be honest I don‚Äôt think she knew what the post was about. When I reached, the atmosphere was festive and celebrations had begun. But my mother just looked at me, hugged me and said, ‚ÄòThe best thing is that you will be back in Gujarat now!‚Äô -- such is a mother‚Äôs nature, that no matter what‚Äôs going on around her, she wants to be close to her children. 
After that she said, ‚ÄòDekh bhai, I don‚Äôt understand what you do, but promise me you will never take a bribe -- don‚Äôt ever commit that sin.‚Äô Those words really impacted me and I‚Äôll tell you why. A woman who has lived in poverty her entire life and who has never had material comforts, during an abundant and celebratory time, asked me to not take a bribe.
So, even after I‚Äôve become Prime Minister, my roots remain strong and relentless. Back in the day, even if someone told my mother that I got an ordinary job somewhere, she would have distributed mithai to the entire village. So CM-VM nothing matters to her -- as long as the human in the Chair strives to be honest and absolute for the country.‚Äù #TheModiStory üì∏courtesy: @officialhumansofbombay
